{"TopicId":153310,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Any tips and tricks??","CreatedByName":"SpaceFanatic10","CreatedById":172379,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T17:11:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFanatic10","CreatedById":172379,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T17:11:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022Lucida Sans Unicode, Lucida Grande, sans-serif\u0022\u003EYo wassup homesicles!\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just wanted to know some tips and tricks for docking in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor example,if i want\u00A0to dock with a space station,i either miss it,or i crash into it,causing me to revert the flight.And even with cheats,its kinda hard to dock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny tips and tricks??? I would appreciate it.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220160805141235_1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022625\u0022 src=\u0022http://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/attachments/19642/20160805141235_1.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T18:24:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRendezvous and docking is either the hardest thing or the easiest thing in KSP. Before you got it down it all seems like some kind of evil dark magic. Once the pieces fall into place you\u0027ll wonder what all the fuzz was about. Watch tutorials and practice practice practice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-10T18:25:11Z\u0022 title=\u002212/10/2016 06:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Tex_NL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starman4308","CreatedById":122674,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T18:46:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA decent\u00A0mod, like \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/40423-12-docking-port-alignment-indicator-version-651-updated-102516/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ENavyfish\u0027s docking port alignment mod\u003C/a\u003E, makes docking significantly easier. I\u0027l be honest: I\u0027d probably be pretty hopeless at docking without it, or at least something similar to it (there\u0027s also a mod to add an indicator to the navball).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martian Emigrant","CreatedById":158362,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T20:20:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne of the things that might help if you don\u0027t do it already.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSwitch ship (To the target) select through \u0022Control from here\u0022 the docking port you want to use. Then make the the other ship target and line up on is port.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRevert to the chaser ship. You can switch back and forth making sure they are in line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you do switch make sure you are \u0022Far\u0022 or \u0022Slow\u0022 collisions happens when you gone (Distracted) too long.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nME\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T22:49:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222882337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481389914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceFanatic10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/10/2016 at 9:11 AM, SpaceFanatic10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just wanted to know some tips and tricks for docking in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA while back, I put together this \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/189763-illustrated-guide-to-docking/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Eillustrated docking tutorial\u003C/a\u003E, which you may find useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-10T23:10:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPractice in hacked gravity first. Make two simple ships, stick\u0027m on the launchpad and runway, hack gravity, give a boost up, and try to dock them. This way you don\u0027t have to worry about getting a rendezvous first. Once you get confident, send them into space on the same vehicle, and dock them. Lastly, send them up on different vehicles and rendezvous and dock them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-11T00:52:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe basic technique is: set up a close approach. As you come zooming in on the close approach, use the navball to adjust the approach (at least once) to make it really close. When you are passing your destination, brake to a dead stop. Use your eyes in flight mode to pick out the location of your docking point. Fly toward it slowly. When you are much closer, brake to a dead stop -- and repeat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd one tip that I don\u0027t think has made it into any docking tutorial yet: go into the context menus of your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports and\u00A0disable\u00A0the roll/pitch/yaw. This allows you to turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E at the same time. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E will keep your nose pointed in a straight line while you use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E system (ijklh and limited thrust) to dock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFanatic10","CreatedById":172379,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-11T07:15:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022154251\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/154251-bewing/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@bewing\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022123837\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/123837-dman979/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dman979\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022158362\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Martian Emigrant\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122674-starman4308/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122674\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122674-starman4308/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Starman4308\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002258254\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/58254-tex_nl/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Tex_NL\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you all so much,i now know how to easily dock in KSP!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:kiss:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_kiss.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:kiss:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draalo","CreatedById":158993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-11T07:38:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022And one tip that I don\u0027t think has made it into any docking tutorial yet: go into the context menus of your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports and\u00A0disable\u00A0the roll/pitch/yaw. This allows you to turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E at the same time. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E will keep your nose pointed in a straight line while you use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E system (ijklh and limited thrust) to dock.\u0022 by bewing\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nahh, thx a lot - was allways annoyed when the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E fires the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E while docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow i dont have to switch \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E on and off and on again while docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gianni1122","CreatedById":170752,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-11T16:45:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome good tips here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/152983-docking/\u0026amp;page=1\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158993-draalo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022158993\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158993-draalo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Draalo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0just a friendly tip; Use your mouse to highlight\u00A0the text you want to \u0022quote\u0022 (like you\u0027re going to copy \u0026amp; paste it) and you should see a small black popup that says \u0022\u003Cu\u003Equote this\u003C/u\u003E\u0022. Use it to make your quotes look like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022125662\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/125662-snark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Snark\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s does above\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-11T17:00:29Z\u0022 title=\u002212/11/2016 05:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 11, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gianni1122\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draalo","CreatedById":158993,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-11T19:50:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222883596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481474736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170752\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gianni1122\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Gianni1122 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse your mouse to highlight\u00A0the text you want to \u0022quote\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nworks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthx \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-12T16:34:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222882916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481417560\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/10/2016 at 4:52 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd one tip that I don\u0027t think has made it into any docking tutorial yet: go into the context menus of your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports and\u00A0disable\u00A0the roll/pitch/yaw. This allows you to turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E at the same time. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E will keep your nose pointed in a straight line while you use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E system (ijklh and limited thrust) to dock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n^ This.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222883188\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481441914\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Draalo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/10/2016 at 11:38 PM, Draalo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow i dont have to switch \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E on and off and on again while docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you can do what I do, and just stick a snippet of ModuleManager config into your GameData folder so that \u0022roll/pitch/yaw \u003Cstrong\u003Edisabled\u003C/strong\u003E\u0022 is the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Edefault\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E state for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters (i.e. they\u0027re already set that way when you add a new one to a ship that you\u0027re building).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen you never have to mess with this ever again, including when you\u0027re building a new ship in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you like the idea, you can find config to do that (along with various other useful things) here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139980-community-database-of-module-manager-patches-for-stock-ksp/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2587116\u0026amp;embedComment=2587116\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2587116\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}